## The White Screen of Death ‚ò†Ô∏è

**Without Error Boundaries**:
One component fails ‚Üí Entire app crashes ‚Üí Blank screen ‚Üí User gone forever

**With Error Boundaries**:
One component fails ‚Üí Error caught ‚Üí Fallback UI ‚Üí User continues ‚Üí Crisis averted

## The Basic Boundary üõ°Ô∏è

```tsx
class ErrorBoundary extends Component {
  state = { hasError: false };

  static getDerivedStateFromError(error) {
    return { hasError: true };
  }

  componentDidCatch(error, errorInfo) {
    console.error('Caught:', error, errorInfo);
    // Send to error tracking
  }

  render() {
    if (this.state.hasError) {
      return <FallbackUI />;
    }
    return this.props.children;
  }
}

// Wrap and protect
<ErrorBoundary>
  <RiskyComponent />
</ErrorBoundary>;
```

